        <body>
            <div xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Tamás Szalaházy (Linz, 7 March 1530)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">1. The news Szalaházy has shared with him about
                            Esztergom and Eger has aggrieved him. Even their hope is lost, he does
                            not know what they could do. 2. He is happy about Veszprém’s defense, he
                            wishes such news was arriving from other places as well.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/EB0B46C7-30D1-4300-A6BE-98473A14286B
                    "/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Ad <persName>Thomam episcopum Agriensem</persName> cancellarium
                    Hungariae.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">[1.] Maximo affectus sum, Reverendissime Pater, maerore, cum tuas
                    hodie accepi litteras, ex quibus ea certo intellexi, quae iam antea rumor ad nos
                    detulerat arcem tuam Agriensem<note xml:id="note.1">Eger.</note> a turba
                    infidelium cum magna nostrorum clade raptam, nostros qui in illis fuerunt
                    regionibus, ab hostibus <choice>
                        <orig>miserime</orig>
                        <supplied>miserrime</supplied>
                    </choice> et pulsos et <choice>
                        <orig>praesecutos</orig>
                        <supplied>persecutos</supplied>
                    </choice>, <placeName>Strigonium</placeName><note xml:id="note.2"
                        >Esztergom.</note> direptum, colonos civitatis et incolas captivos per
                    Turcas crudeliter abductos. Haec et alia multa <del corresp="Olahus">meam
                        quam</del><add corresp="Olahus" type="corr">meum quem</add> antea <del
                        corresp="Olahus">de</del><add corresp="Olahus" type="corr">in</add>
                    similibus conceperam malis, mirum in modum auxerunt <del corresp="Olahus"
                        >tristitiam</del><add corresp="Olahus" type="corr">dolorem</add>. Utinam Deo
                    optimo maximo prospiciente iam tandem aliquis finis his nostris daretur
                    calamitatibus, non modo suspicari, sed ne cogitare possum, quid sit nobis
                    sperandum. Ex omnibus fere partibus, quibus nobis <del corresp="Olahus"
                        >opitulari</del><add corresp="Olahus" type="corr">subveniri</add> posset,
                    non aliud <del corresp="Olahus">praeterquam</del><add corresp="Olahus"
                        type="corr">quam</add> intestinas seditiones, odia mutua, plurima mala
                    audimus, et quid eiusdem malis nobis imminentibus praesidii sperare possumus?
                    Spes, quae sola miseris temporibus homini solatium praebere solet, ea quoque
                    nunc <del corresp="Olahus">non</del><add corresp="Olahus" type="corr"
                        >nobis</add> est erepta. Quare quid sperandum sit, et quid faciendum, non
                    satis possum cogitare.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">[2.] Illud, <add corresp="Olahus" type="insert">quod</add> cum magna
                    hostium clade Wesprimium arx tua, virtute et fortitudine castellanorum<note
                        xml:id="note.3">András Choron of Devecser (before 1500–1552), landlord and
                        one of the most important captains of the Habsburgs in Hungary. He played an
                        important part of the supression of the Dózsa Revolt in 1514. He became <hi
                            rend="italic">viceispán</hi> of Veszprém county in 1523, Captain of
                        castle Sümeg in 1524, and he remained loyal to King Ferdinand I, see <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Varga</hi> 2001a, and <hi rend="smallcap">Varga</hi>
                        2001b.</note> tuorum, optimorum et fidelium virorum conservata sit, gaudeo;
                    utinam ex locis etiam aliis tam iucunda et laeta nobis <del corresp="Olahus"
                        >nuntiaretur</del><add corresp="Olahus" type="corr">nuntiarentur</add>.
                    Nostrum est, si quid aliunde <add corresp="Olahus" type="insert">bonae</add> rei
                    adferatur, mediocriter laetari, in adversis autem non magnopere <add
                        corresp="Olahus" type="insert">animo</add> esse deiecto <del
                        corresp="Olahus">animo</del>. Si quid erit etiam deinceps, Reverendissime
                    Praesul, quod aliquid animi nobis addere posse videatur, rogo fac de eo nos huc
                    certiores. Vale.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.4">Ex <placeName>Lincio</placeName> 7. Martii 1530.</p>
            </div>
